<subSubSection id="D5E96539FF89FFCB6051FE55FE3EAC87" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="9D4C36B2FF89FFCB6051FE55FE3EAC87" blockId="5.[264,1324,502,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6051FE55FE9FAA76" bold="true" box="[264,323,502,528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Size:</emphasis>
Maximum length about 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB6334FE54FD1DAA77" box="[621,705,503,529]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F9624B43FF89FFCB6388FE54FC8AAA77" author="Plate" box="[721,854,503,529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" refString="Plate, L. H. (1899) Die Anatomie und Phylogenie der Chitonen. Fauna Chilensis 2 (1). Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 2, Suppl. 5, 15 - 216, pls 2 - 11." type="journal article" year="1899">
Plate 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB624EFE54FC8AAA77" box="[791,854,503,529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1899.0">1899</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6235FE55FBC9AA76" bold="true" box="[876,1045,502,528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Body outline:</emphasis>
Elongate oval, dorsum round. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6002FDBDFE70AA5E" bold="true" box="[347,428,542,568]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Color:</emphasis>
Cream, normally covered by a darker properiostracum. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6567FDBDFB49AA5E" bold="true" box="[1086,1173,542,568]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Valves:</emphasis>
Rather thin; head valve semicircular, posterior valve margin widely V­shaped, slightly notched in middle, sculptured by approximately 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6399FDCCFD01AAEF" box="[704,733,623,649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="80.0">80</number>
radial ribs of fine roundish granules; intermediate valves rectangular, posterior margin straight, apex not present, lateral areas slightly elevated, with about 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6359FD1CFDC1AABF" box="[512,541,703,729]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="15.0">15</number>
radial rows of granules, central area with about 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6539FD1CFBA1AABF" box="[1120,1149,703,729]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="70.0">70</number>
longitudinally arranged, closely set, roundish granules; tail valve semicircular with mucro centrally, postmucronal slope steep and straight, postmucronal area sculptured like head valve, antemucronal area similar to central area of intermediate valves; growth marks present on terminal valves and lateral areas. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB63FFFCFDFC5CAB1E" bold="true" box="[678,896,862,888]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Articulamentum:</emphasis>
Thin and white. 
<collectingCountry id="E5E47622FF89FFCB6501FCFCFBA5AB1F" box="[1112,1145,863,889]" name="American Samoa" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">As</collectingCountry>
diagnostic for genus insertion plates missing, apophyses well developed. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB629EFC25FB8AABC6" bold="true" box="[967,1110,902,928]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Perinotum:</emphasis>
Dorsally covered with flat, finely ribbed conical scales, up to 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6254FC0CFCC0ABAF" box="[781,796,943,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="6.0">6</number>
ribs, not imbricated. Ventrally with elongate scales arranged in radial rows. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6325FC75FD2EAB96" bold="true" box="[636,754,982,1008]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ctenidia:</emphasis>
Restricted to posterior part of mantle cavity, in contact with anal papillae. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB630FFC5DFD6DAC7E" bold="true" box="[598,689,1022,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Radula</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="FBE2AE77FF89FFCB639FFC5CFCD8AC7F" box="[710,772,1023,1049]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4b7r-7sec" name="Bavarian State Collection of Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">ZSM</collectionCode>
Moll 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB620CFC5CFC12AC7F" box="[853,974,1023,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0050428E7">20050428</number>
; 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB6286FC5CFBFBAC7F" box="[991,1063,1023,1049]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
body length): radula length 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB603BFB84FE15AC27" box="[354,457,1063,1089]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
. Radula cartilage length 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB6249FB84FCAAAC27" box="[784,886,1063,1089]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB62D2FB84FC74AC27" box="[907,936,1063,1089]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="67.0">67</number>
teeth rows, 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB650AFB84FBACAC27" box="[1107,1136,1063,1089]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="51.0">51</number>
of them with mineralized teeth. Central tooth slender and very short, centrally constricted; blade simple and directed inwards. First lateral tooth slightly larger, also with simple inward­directed blade. Second lateral tooth with elongate sharply pointed, bidentate head; outer denticle smaller than inner.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5E96539FF89FFCB6061FB4DFC04AD57" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="9D4C36B2FF89FFCB6061FB4DFC04AD57" blockId="5.[264,1324,502,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6061FB4DFE72AD6E" bold="true" box="[312,430,1262,1288]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Material:</emphasis>
A single specimen (
<collectionCode id="FBE2AE77FF89FFCB63C7FB4CFD00AD6F" box="[670,732,1263,1289]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4b7r-7sec" name="Bavarian State Collection of Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">ZSM</collectionCode>
Moll 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB627DFB4CFC47AD6F" box="[804,923,1263,1289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0050341E7">20050341</number>
) was found at station 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB65C4FB4CFB72AD6F" box="[1181,1198,1263,1289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
, at a depth between 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB6028FAB4FE05AD57" box="[369,473,1303,1329]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25 m</quantity>
on a steep wall under a stone (see 
<tableCitation id="D0710309FF89FFCB6229FAB4FC1AAD57" box="[880,966,1303,1329]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="20.[264,352,443,467]" captionTargetBox="[272,1303,500,864]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 1. Species and specimens collected by station." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C98C663AFF98FFDA6051FE18FC88A9B5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" tableUuid="C98C663AFF98FFDA6051FE18FC88A9B5">
Table 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB62E1FAB4FC1AAD57" box="[952,966,1303,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5E96539FF89FFCB6061FA9DFC3DAE8F" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9D4C36B2FF89FFCB6061FA9DFC3DAE8F" blockId="5.[264,1324,502,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6061FA9DFE06AD3E" bold="true" box="[312,474,1342,1368]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution:</emphasis>
The species occurs in the Magellanic Region south of 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6532FA9CFB50AD3F" box="[1131,1164,1343,1369]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="42.0">42</number>
°S along both sides of South 
<collectingCountry id="E5E47622FF89FFCB60EFFAC4FDC7ADE7" box="[438,539,1383,1409]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">America</collectingCountry>
down to the Straits of Magellan (
<bibRefCitation id="F9624B43FF89FFCB62FFFAC4FB13ADE7" author="Kaas" box="[934,1231,1383,1409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="25" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985 a) Monograph of living chitons. (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) 1, Order Neoloricata: Lepidopleurina, E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">
Kaas &amp; Van Belle 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB65DAFAC4FB1DADE7" box="[1155,1217,1383,1409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1985.0">1985</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). While also reported from the intertidal zone, it generally seems to prefer depths around 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB659BFA2CFAF7ADCF" box="[1218,1323,1423,1449]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="22.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="15.0">15–30 m</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB604BFA14FEE2ADB6" box="[274,318,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">fide</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F9624B43FF89FFCB6013FA14FD97ADB7" author="Reid" box="[330,587,1463,1489]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" refString="Reid, D. G. &amp; Osorio, C. (2000) The shallow-water marine Mollusca of the Estero Elefantes and Laguna San Rafael, southern Chile. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, London (Zoology), 66 (2), 109 - 146." type="journal article" year="2000">
Reid &amp; Osorio 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6354FA14FD97ADB7" box="[525,587,1463,1489]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; this report). Maximum depth is recorded from 
<quantity id="5A0B9B57FF89FFCB65F8FA14FAF7ADB7" box="[1185,1323,1463,1489]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="275.0" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="250.0">250–300 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F9624B43FF89FFCB6049FA7CFE77AD9F" author="Leloup" box="[272,427,1503,1529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" refString="Leloup, E. (1956) Reports of the Lund University Chile Expedition 1948 - 49. 27. Polyplacophora. Lunds Universitets Arsskriften (n. s. (2 )), 52 (15), 1 - 94." type="journal article" year="1956">
Leloup 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB6035FA7CFE77AD9F" box="[364,427,1503,1529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="5AF34D31FF89FFCB6099FA7CFD6AAD9E" box="[448,694,1503,1528]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="medinae">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6099FA7CFD6AAD9E" box="[448,694,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leptochiton medinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits a variety of hard substrata, such as holdfasts of 
<taxonomicName id="5AF34D31FF89FFCB6070F9A4FE6BAE46" box="[297,439,1543,1568]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Laminariaceae" genus="Macrocystis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Laminariales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6070F9A4FE6BAE46" box="[297,439,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Macrocystis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cobbles encrusted with calcareous red algae, or pebbles and shells on silt. 
<taxonomicName id="5AF34D31FF89FFCB6051F98CFDD4AE2E" box="[264,520,1583,1608]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="medinae">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6051F98CFDD4AE2E" box="[264,520,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leptochiton medinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in areas with oceanic salinity levels, and also in hyposalinic locations with only 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB63CBF9F4FD00AE17" box="[658,732,1623,1649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="18.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="15.0">15–22</number>
‰, thus it seems to be tolerant of wide salinity variations. The single record of the species in Comau Fjord does not necessarily mean that it is rare. It is more likely that the species was overlooked, because of its small size and its dark properiostracum, which may provide it with camouflage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5E96539FF89FFC86061F955FDBBA938" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9D4C36B2FF89FFC86061F955FDBBA938" blockId="5.[264,1324,502,1889]" lastBlockId="6.[264,1323,284,350]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB6061F955FE6FAF76" bold="true" box="[312,435,1782,1808]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks:</emphasis>
The species could be easily mistaken for 
<taxonomicName id="5AF34D31FF89FFCB62A6F954FAF7AF76" box="[1023,1323,1783,1808]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Ischnochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="stramineus">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB62A6F954FAF7AF76" box="[1023,1323,1783,1808]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ischnochiton stramineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sowerby in 
<bibRefCitation id="F9624B43FF89FFCB60C6F8BCFD3DAF5F" author="Broderip" box="[415,737,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="24" refString="Broderip, W. J. &amp; Sowerby, G. B. (1832 - 1833) Characters of new species of Mollusca and Conchifera, collected by Mr. Cuming. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 25 - 33, 50 - 61, 104 - 108, 124 - 126 (1832), 173 - 179, 194 - 202 (1833)." type="book chapter" year="1832">
Broderip &amp; Sowerby, 
<number id="2B3B2495FF89FFCB63FBF8BCFD3DAF5F" box="[674,737,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Compared to the latter species, 
<taxonomicName id="5AF34D31FF89FFCB653CF8BCFB3BAF5E" box="[1125,1255,1823,1849]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="medinae">
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB653CF8BCFBA9AF5E" box="[1125,1141,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="AF87EAA0FF89FFCB65DDF8BCFB3BAF5E" box="[1156,1255,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">medinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks insertion plates in the valves, has a much narrower perinotum, the dorsal perinotum scales are of a different form, and the ctenidia differ in their posterior position and in being in contact with the anal papillae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
